A forecaster says the wet weather is expected to last until Monday, especially in Gauteng and other parts of the country. JOHANNESBURG - The South African Weather Service has warned that some South Africans will experience a wet Christmas weekend.The forecaster says there is a good probability of showers and thundershowers in Gauteng, Mpumalanga, Limpopo and North West provinces.Senior forecaster Dipuo Tawana says the wet weather is expected to last until Monday, especially in Gauteng and other parts of the country. There s good probability of showers and thundershowers over Gauteng and Mpumalanga. There s a possibility of heavy falls over the eastern parts on Christmas day. We might even have localised flooding over the Gauteng province. (Edited by Shimoney Regter)